article.headline: Brown 57, Princeton 54
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. -- Matt Mullery scored 15 points and Steve Gruber sank two free throws with 8 seconds left, leading Brown to a 57-54 win over Princeton on Saturday. The Bears (10-17, 4-6 Ivy League) led 55-51 with just less than 20 seconds left, but Patrick Saunders dropped in a layup and Marcus Schroeder sank a free throw to pull the Tigers within one point. Gruber connected on 2 of 2 free throws, though, and Douglas Davis missed a late jumper for the Tigers to seal Brown's win. Peter Sullivan added 13 points and Tucker Halpern had 12 for the Bears, who finished with a 94.7 percent mark from the foul line (18-for-19). The Tigers shot just 57.1 percent from the stripe (4-for-7). Muller was 7-for-7 from the foul line -- one of four Bears to finish perfect at the stripe. Schroeder scored 17 points for the Tigers (16-7, 7-2), who dropped out of first place in the conference.
